extendedInfo.description: NB: Please backup your list before installing v1.6.0! Your list should upgrade automatically but there have been instances on certain devices where a list upgrade has failed and is lost.On Sale Now !!!The most popular printed field guide to North American birds is now available in its entirety on the Android!NB: Please note that an additional download of 360MB is required once this app has been installed. Please ensure you use a WiFi connection to prevent additional data costs.The Sibley Guide to Birds has become the most popular and fastest selling printed guide to birds as well as the most comprehensive and authoritative guide to North American Birds:â Over 6600 images.â Every species is shown perched and in flight from above and below.â Shows every major seasonal, age, and sexual variation.â Detailed coverage of subspecies and regional variations.â Detailed maps showing not just winter and summer range but also migration and rare occurrence.â Detailed descriptions of songs and calls, comparing similar species measurements of length, wingspan, and weight for every species.Now all of that information is available in an easy-to-navigate portable format on any Android device.Includes the following functionality:â Swipe to move to the next or previous species.â One-tap enlargement of images with extended zoom functionality.â Over 2300 carefully-selected and edited sound recordings. Nearly all species are represented with multiple examples showing the range of vocalizations.â The ability to compare any two images, maps, or sounds, side by side on the screen.â The ability to filter by state/province, so that you see only the species likely to occur in your location, and to further reduce the possibilities to the most common birds in that area.â The ability to search by distinguishing features such as size, prominent colors, habits, and group.â *A basic personal species list that stores your sightings saved to the device (ability to upload list coming soon)* Uninstalling/reinstalling the program will result in the loss of your list, it is recommended that you keep your own backup (master list) separate from the application (application provides backup/restore functionality in "My List" page)We go out of our way to resolve customer issues, please feel free to contact us by email at support@mydigitalearth.comWe invite all users to share their comments and ideas on our forum at www.mydigitalearth.com

reviews.title: Fantastic app!
reviews.comment: This app has been incredibly helpful for ID by voice.  I love having Sibley with me all the time without having to carry anything but my phone. Love the update, too!
reviews.author: Inga Holmquist

reviews.title: Worth the money
reviews.comment: Overall I am very impressed with this app. It has all of the info in the printed field guide such as maps of the migration patterns, detailed descriptions, and pictures of different seasonal plumage. Plus having all the calls and songs at your fingertips is incredible in the field!
reviews.author: Taylor Scriber

reviews.title: Awesome App!
reviews.comment: I know this app seems like a lot of money but it is worth every penny. You get the entire guide to birds of North America ($40 value) plus the bird songs. I have the paper version but don\'t use it much anymore because this app is so convenient and easy to use.  If you aren\'t into birding, iBird or the audobon apps might do the trick but this a must have for any serious birders!
reviews.author: Justin Lehman

reviews.title: My goto app
reviews.comment: Have loved Sibley\'s drawings since I bought the original guide back in the day and I love having them on my phone.  It\'s a bit pricey, but I still prefer it to other mobile guides available.
reviews.author: Tom Talbott

reviews.title: Fast app, better than book
reviews.comment: This is truly a well-made app. It loads very quickly and you can search for birds quickly by location characteristic and taxonomy et cetera. They must have for any North America birder.  Has various sounds too, all well implemented and useable.
reviews.author: Alejandro Erickson

reviews.title: Won\'t work without connection
reviews.comment: I took my App to Mexico on my phone and Tablet. My Tablet is only WiFi enabled. The guide would not even start. I tried more phone and it cost me $100 in download fees.  If you expect to use this app outside of your living room don\'t waste the money.
reviews.author: James Moss

reviews.title: Expensive, but worth it
reviews.comment: Best illustrations out there; more information-dense than any photo. Maps are decent and the variety of vocalizations is a great. Offline capability is key and within-app navigation works well. Simple and effective.
reviews.author: Peter Lindstrom

reviews.comment: This is an excellent app based on an excellent book. The illustrations are the absolute best. The calls and songs are very useful and have been expanded several times since I bought the app. The app on my Asus 7 pad now goes every where with me in the field. It is very useful to be able to identify a species by listening to the song in the app. As this app evolves I hope that more geographic diversity in calls will be added.
reviews.author: Paul Eagles

reviews.title: Wonderful App, All you need in the field
reviews.comment: This has greatly improved my bird identification - especially when identifying by ear.  The amount of great recordings you can play back to memorize the bird songs, plus different plumages, range maps, comparison tool, it just works.    It\'s quick (I compared to the Audobon app my friend has - blows it away in speed).  It doesn\'t seem to use any data on my phone, (Samsung S3), in my data usage it doesn\'t even show up.  Not sure how it does this other than it must be pre loading everything via wifi.  This is contradictory to the user below (James Moss)\'s experience - perhaps the tablet version is different?  I just tested my observation by turning off my Wifi and mobile on phone (flight mode), and the app works just as quick and even looking up birds that I have not previously and playing all the sounds, maps, etc.  The best birding app I have ever used.  One thing that would be nice is an easier way to keep life lists, without having to enter all the details of birds previously seen.  My paper field guide will always be my go-to for life lists though.
reviews.author: Paul Baldassi

reviews.title: Not ready for prime time on Android
reviews.comment: I like Sibley\'s paper field guide for Eastern Birds...it\'s my go to book to carry in the field.      But I can\'t understand why so many folks like the Android app.    The songs are great and drawings are regular Sibley quality but the functionality of the search is awful.    Try to search for a bird by \"features\" and you get a choice of 8 color combinations and it doesn\'t include any variation of Brown.   God forbid you\'re trying to ID one of the Sparrows!  Try to choose a size... you can choose \"Sparrow-size\" or \"Thrush-size\" but if it\'s right in between and you\'re not sure... well tough luck, you can only choose one size at a time.  How about the Alphabetic search?   I typed in \"Indigo Bunting\" and got \"No results could be found for your search.\"   Of course if I scroll down to Buntings, it\'s right there...  The list of poor functionality goes on and I can only assume it\'s a better program on the Apple devices.    I gave it 3 stars for the songs and drawings but it\'s such a pita to use I went back to IBird Pro which is way more functional and incidentally less expensive.    I think Sibley is cashing in on his name selling this for $20 and I feel I\'ve been ripped off.
reviews.author: John S

reviews.title: WOWEEEEEE this is GREAT!
reviews.comment: I am a professional naturalist (over 20 years in the field leading bird walks) and have used lots and lots of bird call devices from LP records to tapes to cds to the identi-flyer and even the Cornell Audio books. all of these are wonderful in their own way but some are limited to playing only one or two calls of each bird. in the case of the Northern Cardinal, for example, with at least 8 distinctive calls, this App is Fantastic in that it features a wide array of calls for each species. The range maps are great (key is on each page so i don\'t have to page back if i forget what each color represents) and even contains additional info from Wikipedia for us that are factoid nuts. I highly recommend this App for professionals, educators, backyard bird enthusiasts and anyone looking for a great bird field guide. Thanks Sibley!
reviews.author: Kristi Orcutt

reviews.comment: Impressive app
reviews.author: Jack Hernandez

reviews.title: The first app I install!
reviews.comment: I did not know I needed this app until I used it to identify a Spotted Towhee. Then I couldn\'t do without this app!
reviews.author: Jani Rounds

reviews.title: Much improved interface
reviews.comment: This was already my favorite birding app and the new interface is a great improvement.  Really like integrated calls.  Hardly use my field guide anymore.  No technical issues.
reviews.author: Peter Roberts

reviews.title: March 2013 update
reviews.comment: Love the latest update! Would love to see an option for other formats for GPS coordinates, such as UTMs.
reviews.author: Matthew Amalong

reviews.title: Great App
reviews.comment: I always use this app in place of a field guide while out and about.  It is pretty easy to scan through birds when identifying an unknown species.  The images and descriptions are directly from the Sibley field guides.  Personally, a pocket field guide is no longer necessary once you have this app.
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: Perfect
reviews.comment: Aside from the book itself, this is the best field guide I ever purchased.  Simplicity and convenience in one package.  -- As the updates come through it continues to get even better. Good job on this one.
reviews.author: Tommy RKaid

reviews.title: Poor Usability
reviews.comment: Bought an Android phone so purch Sibley again tho I have it for my Ipod.  Apple version is terrific; Android version is lousy.  I\'m a very active birder who frequently leads outings. With this version I cant easily scroll through plumages and songs often dont play.  This makes this app unreliable and unusable in the field.  Hope I can get my $ back.
reviews.author: Don Gorney

reviews.title: Its the best
reviews.comment: I prefer the Sibley\'s to iBird Pro because of the ease of installation and use. The improved interface makes it even better. When I complained to I bird Pro folks about the download requirements they pretty much told me to get lost. So....#**%&$ them.
reviews.author: Billy Ellis

reviews.title: Excellent
reviews.comment: Worth the money, if like the book u will love this app. Its way better they fix force close. Bought 3 different ones this is the best!
reviews.author: A Google User
